               <floruit >  He is considered to have been the founder of monasticism, born from christian parents in <placeName ref="LOC5219Qimana">Qimān al-ʿArūs</placeName>.  
                  At the gae of 20,  he started to practice ascetic life. He was an ardent supporter of <persName ref="PRS2209Athanasi">Athanasius</persName> 
                  in his fight against Arianism. He is highly respected in the monasticism tradition of <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName>. 
                  The monastic houses of both <persName ref="PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymanot</persName> and <persName ref="PRS3932Ewostate">Ewosṭatewos</persName>
                  trace themselves to <persName ref="PRS1962Anthony">Anthony</persName>. </floruit>
